The paper deals with facial expression recognition using a convolutional neural network, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain. The paper also discusses the use of hand-crafted features and feature extraction methods, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper addresses the challenge of recognizing subtle emotions, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR) domains.
